/023-operator-config-health-logs.md:94:- npm run start:smoke\ndocs/exec-plans/completed/023-operator-config-health-logs.md:120:- 2026-05-05T14:25:00.000Z: found partial `/config`, `/api/health`, and `start:logged` implementations; reused them while adding shared operator config/base URL/logging services, persisted base URL override, public config API, expanded connection guide, and `@operator-config` coverage.\ndocs/references/prd-analysis.md:11:- Deployment should work directly, through Docker Compose on port `3000` with a SQLite data volume, and behind Nginx with TLS termination at the proxy.\ndocs/references/prd-analysis.md:21:- Operator configuration for base URL, root reset, health, logs, Docker/Nginx guidance, Ralph loop handoff, and startup proof.\ndocs/references/prd-analysis.md:29:- Runtime state makes `npm run start:smoke` mandatory; `build` alone is not enough evidence.\nlib/endpoints/validation.ts:42:    addError(errors, field, \"Must be a whole number from 0 to 30000.\");\ndocs/exec-plans/completed/001-endpoint-domain-and-schema.md:42:- `npm run db:prepare` is the deterministic runtime-prep command used by Ralph and startup smoke, so keep the command name stable.\n","exit_code":2,"status":"failed"}}
